The theorem statement is: For $n \geq 4$, any sequence $\sigma$ of calls such that all agents are experts after $\sigma$ must have length at least $2n-4$.

To prove this, we use the fact that if there exists a sequence of length less than $2n-4$ that makes all agents experts, then we can find a minimal such sequence. We'll show that no such minimal sequence can exist.

